SUMMARY:Corridor 13 (PC (Microsoft Windows))
DESCRIPTION:Corridor 13 is a first-person psychological anomaly horror game
  set inside an endless\, abandoned school corridor. Players awaken as a yo
 ung girl trapped in a looping hallway where every detail may be a warning\
 , every sound may signal danger\, and every wrong decision sends them back
  or kill them.\n\nTo escape\, players must carefully observe their surroun
 dings and decide whether to continue forward or turn back. If everything a
 ppears normal\, they move on. If something is wrong\, they must retreat. R
 eaching Corridor 13 requires twelve correct decisions in a row — but as th
 e loop progresses\, the anomalies become increasingly dangerous.\n\nUnlike
  traditional “spot the difference” horror games\, Corridor 13 introduces h
 ostile paranormal encounters\, environmental traps\, chase sequences\, uns
 ettling audio cues\, and escalating supernatural events. Whispering childr
 en\, flickering fluorescent lights\, flooded rooms\, mirror-based anomalie
 s\, and humanoid figures lurking in the darkness turn the familiar school 
 setting into a place where memory and perception can no longer be trusted.
 \n\nBuilt in Godot by a solo developer from Germany\, Corridor 13 is desig
 ned for fans of psychological horror\, liminal spaces\, anomaly games\, Ba
 ckrooms-style atmosphere\, and tense first-person horror experiences. The 
 game features 40+ planned anomalies\, randomized progression-based anomaly
  pools\, and Endless and Hardcore modes.\n\nhttps://www.igdb.com/games/cor
 ridor-13
END:VEVENT
